    <h5><strong>What is iBaleka?</strong></h5>
    <div class="divider"></div>
</div>
<div class="xabisohila">
    <p>
        iBaleka is a health and fitness application focused hugely on running.
        It grew from the need for users to better manage their marathons and triathlon in a cleaner manner, something more modern,
        responsive, and sophisticated. The existing solutions that are currently in place do provide the services that our application offers,
        but they don’t provide all the functions in one solution.
    </p>
    <p>
        The category as a whole is considered as a grey area in applications
        development, especially in our own local environment, so the market still requires more innovation. We wanted to make iBaleka's
        focus be wider than most of these applications.
    </p>
    <p>
        The system allows the user to plot running routes,which will allow our mobile users to access created routes via our android application
        and use them to run.
        The system let users organize running events which allow other users to participate.
    </p>
    <p>
        That’s where our system comes into effect. The interface that we provide supports all the mentioned functions and as a benefit
        will reduce the need for many assorted applications.
        It is catered to people who run/jog whether it is professionally or casually and is accessible anytime they find need of it
        anywhere they are.
    </p>
    <p>
        The current user will be able to use the application to record their running activities and provide them with a usable
        interface that will show them reports on their past runs,routes that they ran and events created.
        It will also allow them to plot their routes in advance, which will show the total distance, and will be saveable
        for future reference. Users are able to create running events which allow other users to participate and reflect on each
        other’s running history. Lastly the user will be able to manage their profile and upload a minimal amount of pictures to
        brag about their running progress.
    </p>

</div>
